Basic intro to transformers

Most modern LLM archi depends on the transformers archi.

- transformers archi is most needed.

takes input.
preprcoessing text - Input texts into tokens each token has id.
Encoders - takes input text(tokens) data and produce text encodings
Vector Embeddings - converts those all tokens into Vectors - here symantic meanings between words and captured just like KNN.

transformer archi mainly consists of :
- Encoders - encodes input text into Vectors
- Decoder - generates output text from Vectors

A note of self-attention mechanism:
- Key part of transformers  allows model to weigh importance of diff words/tokens relative to each other.
- This enables models capture long range of dependencies
- above two are key parts of the predicts of next words or tokens.

Variations of transformer models
- BERT - Bi-directional encoder representations from transformers -- predicts hidden words in a given sentence
- GPT models - generative pretrained transformers - Generates new words.

BERT - can do very well of sentimental analysis and also it can find hidden words and also give attention to every word. it can look from both sides - depth understanding - it has encoder
GPT - it looks sentence from left to right - it has decoder.


transformers vs LLMs
- Not all transformers are LLMs
- transformers are also used for CV.

CNN vs transformers
- for vision related tasks VIt is performing better than CNN.

- Not all LLMs are transformers.
- LLMs can be based on recurrent or CNN as well.